        "raw_output": "Based on the EKS Operational Review skill, here are the 12 best practices sections evaluated during a review:\n\n## Core Sections (1\u20139)\n\n1. **Security** \u2014 IAM & Access Management (auth mode, Access Entries, aws-auth, Pod Identity, IRSA, RBAC, STS), Pod Security, Runtime Security, Network Security, Multi-tenancy, Detective Controls, Infrastructure Security (private endpoint, IMDSv2, AMI), Data Encryption (KMS, EBS), Image Security (ECR scanning)\n\n2. **Reliability** \u2014 Applications (probes, PDBs, TopologySpreadConstraints, graceful shutdown, resource requests/limits), Control Plane (version, logs, insights, API latency/throttling), Data Plane (multi-AZ, managed node groups, autoscaling, failed nodes)\n\n3. **Karpenter** \u2014 NodePool config (consolidationPolicy, disruption budgets, instance diversity, Spot, AZ spread, limits), EC2NodeClass (amiFamily, blockDeviceMappings, metadataOptions, selectors, AMI age)\n\n4. **Cluster Autoscaler** \u2014 Deployment, expander strategy, scale-down settings, balance-similar-node-groups, version compatibility\n\n5. **EKS Auto Mode** \u2014 Auto mode status, node pool config, disruption controls\n\n6. **Networking** \u2014 VPC CNI version/config, prefix delegation, subnet IP availability, VPC CIDR sizing, CoreDNS, VPC endpoints, NAT redundancy\n\n7. **Scalability** \u2014 Control plane (API throttling, CRD count), Data plane (scaling headroom, instance diversity, NodePool limits), Cluster services (CoreDNS, metrics-server, addons), Workloads (HPA, resource requests, restart counts), Data Plane Scaling specifics (autoscaling, instance diversity, T-series, AMI updates, EBS, patching)\n\n8. **Cluster Upgrades** \u2014 Version currency (N-1/N-2/N-3), Upgrade Insights, addon compatibility, deprecated APIs, PDB coverage, node group update strategy\n\n9. **Cost Optimization** \u2014 Resource utilization (under/over-utilized), instance right-sizing, Spot adoption, Graviton migration, storage (gp2\u2